# .claude-github-config-ignore
#
# Files listed here are never overwritten when running the claude-github-config
# update workflow or re-running install.sh.
#
# Use this to protect files you have intentionally customized beyond the
# template defaults. Glob patterns are supported (e.g. .claude/skills/my-skill/*).
#
# Examples:
#   doc/PROJECT.md                          ← project-specific, always custom
#   CONTRIBUTING.md                         ← if you've added tech stack details
#   .claude/settings.json                   ← if you've added allowed commands
#   .github/workflows/checklist-to-ready.yml ← if you've modified the workflow
#
# Files you ADD to the repo (not in the template) are never touched regardless
# of this file — the installer only processes files that exist in the template.

doc/PROJECT.md